Our common goal We want Quirky People to be a safe, welcoming, and supportive place where neurodivergent people can connect. To help us keep this space positive, we ask you to keep these guidelines in mind. Respect and empathy Be kind and respectful to everyone. Remember that everyone has different experiences and sensitivities.\nâ€¢ Try to understand others\' points of view, even if you don\'t agree. Assume good intentions.\nâ€¢ Be aware that communication styles can vary greatly. Be patient and ask for clarification if something is unclear, without judgment.\nâ€¢ Avoid generalizations about neurodiversity or groups of people. Clear and mindful communication (Marshall Rosenberg) Express your thoughts, feelings, and needs clearly and respectfully. Using \"I feel...\" or \"I need...\" statements can help.\nâ€¢ Respect others\' boundaries. If someone expresses a limit or asks for space, please respect it.\nâ€¢ It\'s okay to need time to respond to messages. Don\'t pressure others for an immediate reply and feel free to take your time. Handling disagreements It\'s normal to have different opinions. Focus on mutual understanding rather than \"winning\" an argument.\nâ€¢ Express disagreement constructively, without personal attacks, insults, or invalidating others\' experiences.\nâ€¢ If a conversation becomes too difficult or stressful, it\'s okay to take a break or respectfully withdraw. What is not accepted Harassment, bullying, hate speech, discrimination of any kind.\nâ€¢ Spam or excessive promotion.\nâ€¢ Illegal content, unsolicited explicit content, or inappropriate content.\nâ€¢ Sharing others\' private information without consent. Reporting and moderation Use the \"Report User\" feature if you see behavior that violates these guidelines. Reports help us keep the community safe.\nâ€¢ We review reports and take appropriate action, which may include warnings or removal from the app. Take care of yourself Remember to take breaks if you need them.\n Manage your notifi